message.text:
#Hiragana Master
Say it Together! Basic Japanese Words in Japanese Alphabetical Order.
Today's Word is "RA" RAMEN　#nihongo #ramen #らーめん
日本の単語を五十音順にわかりやすく紹介！「ら」ーめん（ラーメン、noodle)
http://eng.nihongodecarenavi.jp/jpn/entry_1398.html

Ramen is noodle dish which has been transformed uniquely in Japan.
It is said that Mitsukuni Tokugawa in Edo era, also known as Mito Komon, was the first Japanese who ate Ramen in Japan. 300 years later, Ramen has been improved dramatically; the instant noodle was invented in 1958, and now it even made it into space as space food!

There are approximately 35,000 Ramen restaurants in Japan, and in Tokyo alone, there are still many Ramen Battleground including Ikebukuro along with Shinjuku and Waseda.
Recently Gotochi（ご当地、local) Ramen which offers different local specialties are also popular.
Why don't you try a Ramen Tour in Japan?

------------
らーめんは日本で独特の進化を遂げた麺料理。日本で一番最初にらーめんを食べたのは、江戸時代の徳川光圀（水戸黄門）と言われています。それから約300年、ラーメンも大きく変わり、1958年にはインスタントヌードル開発、今では宇宙食にもなっています！

日本全国にはラーメン専門店が35,000軒もあり、東京だけでも池袋、新宿、早稲田など、ラーメン激戦区があって行列ができるお店もありますよ。最近では、ご当地ラーメンと呼ばれる地域の味を生かしたラーメンも人気。
日本でラーメンツアーしてみてもおもしろいかも！？
